      "content": "If the inspection uncovers a big, bad problem, like foundation issues, that earnest money doesn't just vanish into the ether, you don't worry. It's not just sitting there like a forgotten pile of loose coins. It gets held in escrow, and the terms of your contract—the paperwork, you know, the fine print—dictate what happens next. Usually, if the inspection reveals a material defect that justifies renegotiation or termination, the escrow agent will facilitate the return of those funds to you, or they might be used to cover certain costs, depending on what the contract says.",
